		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.manton.org/?p=3025</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Here&#8217;s a wonderful video of Glen Keane drawing with VR goggles. I&#8217;ve been watching and listening to Glen explain animation for a long time, on bonus videos going back to my small collection of Disney feature LaserDiscs. It&#8217;s great to see him still in the spotlight after leaving Disney, and the great work he did [&#8230;]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Here&#8217;s a wonderful video of <a href="http://www.cartoonbrew.com/tech/watch-glen-keane-draw-ariel-and-the-beast-in-3d-119110.html">Glen Keane drawing with VR goggles</a>. I&#8217;ve been watching and listening to Glen explain animation for a long time, on bonus videos going back to my small collection of Disney feature LaserDiscs. It&#8217;s great to see him still in the spotlight after leaving Disney, and the great work he did on last year&#8217;s <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O9CG_PoEWCg">Duet</a>.</p>
<p>Speaking of the Disney company, I really enjoyed last night&#8217;s <a href="http://www.pbs.org/waltdisney">American Experience on Walt</a>. Part 2 airs tonight on PBS.</p>
<p><strong>Update</strong>: Shortly after posting this, <a href="http://www.cartoonbrew.com/cartoon-brew-pick/nephtali-by-glen-keane-119359.html">a new film</a> from Glen Keane showed up in my newsreader. It&#8217;s a good month for animation.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
